Around 400 people work in the plant. The chemical plant has made headlines in the past - for example, when methanethiol gas escaped through a leak in 2013 and the area smelled far and wide of rotten eggs. In 2015, around 2,000 liters of mineral oil flowed into the city&#39;s sewage system after an industrial accident.
