According to the paper from the office of Defense Secretary Peter Tauber from the CDU, two weapons, a weapon part and 3474 rounds of ammunition have reappeared so far. The weapons and parts of weapons that have still disappeared include six MG3 machine guns, eleven G3 rifles, four G36 rifles, six signal pistols and two P8 pistols. In addition, 30 weapon barrels for machine guns of the type MG3 are missing.
The extent of weapons and ammunition losses in the Bundeswehr is &quot;scary&quot;, said the left-wing member of the Bundestag Martina Renner. This applies all the more since hardly anything was found again in the course of investigations. The left-wing politician spoke of a &quot;poor balance sheet&quot;. Renner criticized the fact that it was not clear from the list whether the ammunition that had disappeared was found in connection with the investigation into the Bundeswehr officer Franco A., who was suspected of being a terrorist. &quot;Even though a supporter of Franco A. was recently convicted of possessing this ammunition,&quot; said Renner.
