India is blocking a better future with its protectionist economic policy.
India would actually be predestined to be a &quot;war profiteer&quot;. In view of the punitive tariffs that America&#39;s President Donald Trump is imposing on Chinese manufacturers, foreign producers in the People&#39;s Republic feel compelled to change their plans. CFOs of Asian companies considering moving production from China to another country named India as one of the preferred alternatives in a UBS survey. Of course, this has nothing to do with the imponderables of the Sino-US trade war. With a huge pool of young workers and a domestic market of 1.3 billion consumers, India seems destined to play a more important role in the global production chain.
