A sense of justice and courage are high virtues, even in the 21st century, in a world full of war and smoke factories that are warming the climate. It is all the more astonishing that a 16-year-old girl is holding the mirror in front of the powerful people of the time. But what is behind it? Is it helpfulness or clever marketing of a climate activist? Historical feat or manipulative tactic for its own sake?
On the one hand, Greta Thunberg is getting the masses moving and young people standing up for a better climate-friendly world. Historically, it is not the first time in Europe that a young person has managed to win over a crowd of children and young people. As early as 1212, a child named Nikolaus from Cologne felt he had been chosen to work for a more just world. At that time, he was also able to win over a group of young people and persuaded them to cross the sea to get to the promised land, similar to how Greta Thunberg recently made a journey to America with a sailing boat.
