According to medical experts, climate change will put the healthcare system to the test in the future. The climate changes are &quot;definitely&quot; one of the biggest challenges for the health system in the next 20 to 50 years, said Andreas Zeiher, President of the German Society of Cardiology. The cardiovascular system in particular was affected by high temperatures and large jumps in temperature within a short period of time, leading to an increased number of heart attacks. Above all, people with cardiovascular diseases, the elderly and diabetics are affected.
